      "writtenOn": "2022-01-11T16:54:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "i thought the goal was a read-only mount, not a no-exec mount ?",
      "revId": "5918b6479fdc1016efe23b217f016563e855775e",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "59c72465_8c626339",
        "filename": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 1299283
      },
      "writtenOn": "2022-01-11T21:17:10Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We chose no-exec because in the test image environment, the root-fs isn\u0027t always mounted read-only and we wanted to support more than CrOS. Also, the exec permission maps well to the risks associated with a writable configuration.",
      "parentUuid": "cc2266ae_a33b8c3a",
      "revId": "5918b6479fdc1016efe23b217f016563e855775e",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a09d941d_ea359771",
        "filename": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 1040868
      },
      "writtenOn": "2022-01-12T00:16:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e the exec permission maps well to the risks associated with a writable configuration.\n\ndoes it really ?  /mnt/stateful_partition (i.e. /var) as well as /tmp and /run are all noexec.  i thought we specifically didn\u0027t want our daemons writing \u0026 reading configs from these locations.",
      "parentUuid": "59c72465_8c626339",
      "revId": "5918b6479fdc1016efe23b217f016563e855775e",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b0238bfc_f21a3bca",
        "filename": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 1889710
      },
      "writtenOn": "2022-01-12T19:13:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Sounds like we want to revisit our discussion in the DD\u0027s security section. https://docs.google.com/document/d/1M7gdX7Q_PDkQd1PczcDMUG4UAYpxnUBL5B0-pWBNrDY/edit#heading\u003dh.7nky7vaucua0\n\nPreviously read-only mount checks are ruled out due to dev mode CrOS rootfs is rw, and no-exec is decided to be a sensible starting point.",
      "parentUuid": "a09d941d_ea359771",
      "revId": "5918b6479fdc1016efe23b217f016563e855775e",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "61aa4339_bfac5a3f",
        "filename": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 1299283
      },
      "writtenOn": "2022-01-12T19:20:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e does it really ?  /mnt/stateful_partition (i.e. /var) as well as /tmp and /run are all noexec.  i thought we specifically didn\u0027t want our daemons writing \u0026 reading configs from these locations.\n\nMy wording may not have been clear. We want to block no-exec mounts and allow mounts that are executable (e.g. the root-fs) even when they are writeable like after cros-deploy.",
      "parentUuid": "b0238bfc_f21a3bca",
      "revId": "5918b6479fdc1016efe23b217f016563e855775e",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6d4ccbd9_46b995c9",
        "filename": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 1040868
      },
      "writtenOn": "2022-01-13T08:39:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "OK ... that\u0027s not what the CL is doing though :)\n\nthe design doc also has the conclusion inverted.  so i guess that\u0027s the source of the confusion.",
      "parentUuid": "61aa4339_bfac5a3f",
      "revId": "5918b6479fdc1016efe23b217f016563e855775e",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1a3386f4_72c5d3e9",
        "filename": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 1076138
      },
      "writtenOn": "2022-01-13T21:55:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We probably want to tie this to cros_debug or something.\n\nWe want to make sure that people don\u0027t accidentally put the config file in a writable partition in production.\n\nWe don\u0027t want to make the system unbootable when we remount / RW after cros deploy.\n\nSo it sounds like we want to identify a debug flag that allows config files to live in a writable directory, but unless that flag is present, config files have to live in a RO dir (or just be in the rootfs.)",
      "parentUuid": "6d4ccbd9_46b995c9",
      "revId": "5918b6479fdc1016efe23b217f016563e855775e",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ac553b20_0bdab153",
        "filename": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 1299283
      },
      "writtenOn": "2022-01-13T22:32:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t think checking cros_debug is necessary if we check if the configs are from an executable mount (a mount without noexec).",
      "parentUuid": "1a3386f4_72c5d3e9",
      "revId": "5918b6479fdc1016efe23b217f016563e855775e",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "56d56a90_00b0d91e",
        "filename": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 1076138
      },
      "writtenOn": "2022-01-13T22:37:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "That\u0027s fair but at the same time we\u0027re now fully mounting this protection directly on top of our W^X guarantees, instead of making it additive.\n\nI.e. if we fail to prevent a W+X mount, now our protection for config files goes away, whereas if we check for st_dev, we don\u0027t.",
      "parentUuid": "ac553b20_0bdab153",
      "revId": "5918b6479fdc1016efe23b217f016563e855775e",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889"
    },
